{"lemma":"سَبِطٌ","slug":"سَبِطٌ","root":"س.ب.ط","root_slug":"س-ب-ط","root_link":"/words/roots/س-ب-ط","pos":"ADJ","pos_camel":"adj","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":5,"pos_tags":["adj","noun","verb"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":15},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n18728"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B3%D9%8E%D8%A8%D9%90%D8%B7%D9%8C"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to be lanky"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to be well-shaped, to be graceful"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to be liberal, to be bountiful, to be munificent, to be generous"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to miscarry"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"lanky"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"well-shaped, graceful"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"liberal, bountiful, munificent, generous"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"buffelgrasses (Cenchrus gen. et spp.)","tags":["collective"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"Stipagrostis spp.","tags":["collective"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"grandchild from the mother's side"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"grandchild"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"tribe of the Israelites"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"Shia imam (grandchild of the prophet)","examples":[{"text":"أَيُّهَا النَّاسُ أُعْطِينَا سِتًّا وَفُضِّلْنَا بِسَبْعٍ أُعْطِينَا الْعِلْمَ وَالْحِلْمَ وَالسَّمَاحَةَ وَالْفَصَاحَةَ وَالشَّجَاعَةَ وَالْمَحَبَّةَ فِي قُلُوبِ الْمُؤْمِنِينَ وَفُضِّلْنَا بِأَنَّ مِنَّا النَّبِيَّ الْمُخْتَارَ مُحَمَّدًا وَمِنَّا الصِّدِيقَ وَمِنَّا الطَّيَارَ وَمِنَّا أَسَدَ اللهِ وَأَسَدَ رَسُولِهِ وَمِنَّا سِبْطَا هٰذِهِ الْأُمَّةِ مَنْ عَرَفَنِي فَقَدْ عَرَفَنِي وَمَنْ لَمْ يَعْرِفْنِي أَنْبَأْتُهُ بِحَسَبِيّ وَنَسَبِيّ"}]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"Shia imam (grandchild of the prophet); al-Ḥusayn ibn ʿAlī or al-Ḥasan ibn ʿAlī","tags":["definite","especially"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"wand, staff","tags":["rare"]}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Inherited from Proto-Semitic *šabṭ- (literally “staff, rod”). Semantically influenced by Hebrew שֵׁבֶט (śeḇeṭ, “tribe of Israel; staff, sceptre”)."},"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n18728","headword_ar":"سَبِطٌ","root":"sbT","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saboTN","text_ar":"سَبْطٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sabaTN","text_ar":"سَبَطٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (the first and third of these in one copy of the S, and the second alone in another copy of the S, and all in the M and Msb and K,) the first of the dial. of El- Hijáz, (TA,) from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sabiTa","text_ar":"سَبِطَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and the second from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sabuTa","text_ar":"سَبُطَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", the last being an inf. n. used as an epithet, (Msb,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Lank, not crisp;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, M, * Msb, K; *) applied to hair: (S, Msb:) pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sibaATN","text_ar":"سِبَاطٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", which is said by Sb to be of the measure most common for a pl. of an epithet of the measure"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faEalN","text_ar":"فَعَلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (M,) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faEolN","text_ar":"فَعْلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sabiTu Al$~aEari","text_ar":"سَبِطُ الشَّعَرِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, M,) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saboTuhu","text_ar":"سَبْطُهُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (M,) A man"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"having lank hair:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, M:) and in like manner"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sibaATN","text_ar":"سِبَاطٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", alone, applied to a number of persons. (TA.) ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saboTN","text_ar":"سَبْطٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"is also metonymically applied to (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A foreigner,"},{"kind":"text","text":"like as [its contr.]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jaEodN","text_ar":"جَعْدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is to an Arab. (TA.) ―         -b3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sabiTN","text_ar":"سَبِطٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"also signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Tall;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K;) applied to a man: (M:) or, as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saboTN","text_ar":"سَبْطٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (TA,) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sabiTu Aljisomi","text_ar":"سَبِطُ الجِسْمِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (M,) so applied,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"long in the"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"bones called"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^alowaAH","text_ar":"اَلْوَاح"},{"kind":"text","text":"[pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lawoH","text_ar":"لَوْح"},{"kind":"text","text":"], (M, TA,]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and even therein:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sabiTu Aljisomi","text_ar":"سَبِطُ الجِسْمِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"or ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saboTuhu","text_ar":"سَبْطُهُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (accord. to different copies of the K,) or both, (S, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"goodly in stature,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"person,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"proportion,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and evenness."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S.) Also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Having extended limbs, and perfect in make."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sabiTu AlqaSabi","text_ar":"سَبِطُ القَصَبِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saboTuhaA","text_ar":"سَبْطُهَا","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", A man ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"long and even,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"extended, and without protuberances, in the bones of the fore arms and the shanks."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sabiTu AlbanaAni","text_ar":"سَبِطُ البَنَانِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saboTuhaA","text_ar":"سَبْطُهَا","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Long in the fingers."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sabiTu","text_ar":"سَبِطُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alxaloqi","text_ar":"الخَلْقِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"A man"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"lank in make:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(L in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rd","text_ar":"رد"},{"kind":"text","text":":) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sabiTapu Alxaloqi","text_ar":"سَبِطَةُ الخَلْقِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saboTatuhu","text_ar":"سَبْطَتُهُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (tropical:)  a woman"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"lank,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"soft,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"tender, in make."},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, Z, TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sabiTu","text_ar":"سَبِطُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Als~aAqayoni","text_ar":"السَّاقَيْنِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"A man"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"soft,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"flaccid,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"uncompact, in the shanks."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Ham p. 238.) ―         -b4-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alyadayoni","text_ar":"اليَدَيْنِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saboTu","text_ar":"سَبْطُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (M, K, TA,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sabiTuhumaA","text_ar":"سَبِطُهُمَا"},{"kind":"text","text":", (TA, and so in the CK,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sabiTu Alkaf~ayoni","text_ar":"سَبِطُ الكَفَّيْنِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (TA,) (tropical:)  A man who is"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"liberal, bountiful,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"munificent."},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K, TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sabiTN","text_ar":"سَبِطٌ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"biAlomaEoruwfi","text_ar":"بِالْمَعْرُوفِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)  A man"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"easy,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"facile, in beneficence."},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, TA.) ―         -b5-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maTarN sabiTN","text_ar":"مَطَرٌ سَبِطٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Sh, TA,) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saboTN","text_ar":"سَبْطٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Sh, K,) (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Rain pouring abundantly and extensively,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Sh, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and consecutively."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Sh, TA.)"}],"source_refs":["TA","Msb","S","M","K","Sh"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}